summary: This is an email from July 9, 2019, regarding coordination of victim services for the Epstein case. It indicates that law enforcement (a Case Agent) is traveling to Florida for scheduled interviews with potential victims, though no victims have yet requested services.

persons.name: Case AgentMlind
persons.context: The email mentions that the sender just spoke to the Case Agent, who is heading to Florida for interviews scheduled for Thursday.

events.title: Scheduled Victim Interviews in Florida
events.description: The Case Agent is traveling to Florida for interviews with potential Epstein victims scheduled for Thursday.

keyFacts: As of July 9, 2019, no victims in the West Palm/Miami area had yet requested services related to the Epstein case.
A law enforcement Case Agent was traveling to Florida for scheduled victim interviews on the upcoming Thursday.
The correspondence shows proactive coordination between agencies to provide victim services in anticipation of requests following investigative interviews.
